# Hyphae Project Rules

## Git
- NEVER run any git commands (add, commit, push, revert, rebase, etc.). The user manages git themselves.

## Code Changes
- Make minimal, focused changes that get the job done. No over-engineering.
- Prioritise correctness first, then privacy, then performance.
- Do not refactor or restructure code unless explicitly asked.
- Do not add comments that just narrate what the code does.

## Privacy
- Sensitive data (PDFs, experiment logs, hardware notes) must NEVER be sent to cloud APIs.
- Only abstract/sanitised queries go to Gemini. Raw experiments stay local.
- Never log, print, or persist API keys, tokens, or secrets.
- Never hardcode credentials. Use environment variables.

## Performance
- Maximise on-device inference (FunctionGemma via Cactus) to reduce latency and cloud dependency.
- Cloud fallback (Gemini) is a last resort when local confidence is insufficient.
- Keep the `generate_hybrid()` signature unchanged — it must stay compatible with `benchmark.py`.

## Environment
- Python venv lives at `cactus/venv/`. Always activate it before running scripts.
- The `cactus/` directory is a symlink to the cactus repo and is gitignored.
- Gemini model is `gemini-2.5-flash` (not `gemini-2.0-flash`, which is deprecated).

## Testing
- Run `python benchmark.py` to validate changes against the scoring rubric.
- Score = F1 (60%) + speed (15%) + on-device ratio (25%), weighted by difficulty.
